{
  "texts": [
    "Another practical issue is deciding how many runs are sufficient to obtain stable variance estimates.",
    "Too few runs may underestimate epistemic variability, while too many runs can be prohibitively expensive.",
    "2) Sampling from the conditional distribution.",
    "Probabilistic generative models allow multiple imputations to be drawn from a fixed, trained model.",
    "This probes aleatoric uncertainty, as the parameters are held fixed and randomness enters through the latent space or injected noise."
  ]
}